00:15:24.036 --> 00:15:25.160
Maybe, can I stand up here?

00:15:25.160 --> 00:15:26.743
I have some problem
with the eyesight.

00:15:26.743 --> 00:15:29.950
It's difficult for me
to see on the screen.

00:15:29.950 --> 00:15:33.950
OK, here is the history of
colliders-- electron-positron

00:15:33.950 --> 00:15:39.440
colliders in blue and center
of mass and Hadron Colliders--

00:15:39.440 --> 00:15:41.030
proton colliders in red.

00:15:41.030 --> 00:15:45.110
And this is a logarithmic scale
of the center of mass energy.

00:15:45.110 --> 00:15:49.170
Over the last 50 or 60 years,
you can see dramatic progress

00:15:49.170 --> 00:15:50.310
in the collision energy.

00:15:50.310 --> 00:15:53.450
So we got
[? effect our source ?]

00:15:53.450 --> 00:15:56.240
in the energy of
electron-positron collisions

00:15:56.240 --> 00:15:59.115
and the factor of a hundred
in the energy of Hadron

00:15:59.115 --> 00:16:00.817
Colliders-- slightly above 100.

00:16:00.817 --> 00:16:02.650
And there were not so
many-- as you can see,

00:16:02.650 --> 00:16:04.310
there were not so
many Hadron Colliders

00:16:04.310 --> 00:16:08.250
and there used to be more
electron-positron colliders.

00:16:08.250 --> 00:16:11.230
And these colliders seem
successful because they allowed

00:16:11.230 --> 00:16:13.620
us to construct a so-called
standard model of particle

00:16:13.620 --> 00:16:14.580
physics.

00:16:14.580 --> 00:16:17.260
In the standard model,
we have meta-particles,

00:16:17.260 --> 00:16:19.170
which consists of
quarks and leptons

00:16:19.170 --> 00:16:23.940
and we have force carriers
which are these bosons here.

00:16:23.940 --> 00:16:27.320
And then there is a different
particles, the six boson, which

00:16:27.320 --> 00:16:29.229
is neither matter nore force.

00:16:29.229 --> 00:16:31.020
It is completely
different from the others.

00:16:31.020 --> 00:16:33.620
So many of these-- all
the heavier particles here

00:16:33.620 --> 00:16:36.270
they discovered as
colliders. [INAUDIBLE]

00:16:36.270 --> 00:16:39.730
discovered the quark,
and to Tau lepton,

00:16:39.730 --> 00:16:41.292
Petra discovered the gruong.

00:16:41.292 --> 00:16:42.500
That was in Europe-- at DESY.

00:16:42.500 --> 00:16:44.110
That was the only
such discovery which

00:16:44.110 --> 00:16:48.220
didn't give a Nobel
Prize for some reason.

00:16:48.220 --> 00:16:53.340
Then the SPP at CERN
discovered the NW Boson.

00:16:53.340 --> 00:16:55.310
Tevatron discovered
the top quark.

00:16:55.310 --> 00:16:56.790
And then the LHC,
as you may know,

00:16:56.790 --> 00:17:00.485
a few years ago, discovered this
new particle, the Higgs boson.

00:17:00.485 --> 00:17:03.030
So the colliders
were essentially

00:17:03.030 --> 00:17:05.990
in unraveling this
part-- the heavier

00:17:05.990 --> 00:17:07.700
part of the standard model.

00:17:07.700 --> 00:17:10.460
And they have proven a powerful
instrument for discovery

00:17:10.460 --> 00:17:14.170
and for precision measurement.

00:17:14.170 --> 00:17:17.270
OK-- we have the standard
model, but many questions

00:17:17.270 --> 00:17:18.940
are not explained by
the standard model.

00:17:18.940 --> 00:17:20.230
Here's an incomplete list.

00:17:20.230 --> 00:17:22.579
So the standard model only
describes the known matter--

00:17:22.579 --> 00:17:25.699
the visible matter, which
is about 5% of the universe.

00:17:25.699 --> 00:17:27.240
There's a large
part, which is called

00:17:27.240 --> 00:17:29.650
dark matter, which is visible
in the rotational speed

00:17:29.650 --> 00:17:30.410
of the galaxies.

00:17:30.410 --> 00:17:34.430
If you believe in
Newton and Einstein,

00:17:34.430 --> 00:17:36.440
then you need additional
matter to explain

00:17:36.440 --> 00:17:39.750
the observed rotational
velocity seen in the universe.

00:17:39.750 --> 00:17:42.430
And then in addition, there is
something called dark energy.

00:17:42.430 --> 00:17:45.870
I think that maybe later we
can explain the dark energy.

00:17:45.870 --> 00:17:49.890
That comprises even larger--
this comprises even larger part

00:17:49.890 --> 00:17:51.770
of the unknown.

00:17:51.770 --> 00:17:56.702
So maybe 3/4 of the energy of
the universe is dark energy

00:17:56.702 --> 00:17:57.910
and we don't know what it is.

00:17:57.910 --> 00:17:58.900
And then we have more matter.

00:17:58.900 --> 00:17:59.733
We have only matter.

00:17:59.733 --> 00:18:01.130
We have no
anti-matter-- planets,

00:18:01.130 --> 00:18:04.750
anti-matter-- why do we have
matter and not anti-matter?

00:18:04.750 --> 00:18:07.350
And why do the masses of
these fundamental particles

00:18:07.350 --> 00:18:10.820
differ by certain
orders of magnitude.

00:18:10.820 --> 00:18:13.690
Anyway, gravity is not really
included in the standard model.

00:18:13.690 --> 00:18:17.710
And it's very difficult to
combine it with quantum physics

00:18:17.710 --> 00:18:19.010
and with the forces.

00:18:19.010 --> 00:18:22.590
And then there's a search
for word equation, which

00:18:22.590 --> 00:18:26.320
has so not been accomplished.

00:18:26.320 --> 00:18:28.760
Although I think
that some people

00:18:28.760 --> 00:18:32.850
tried to develop it
100 years ago already.

00:18:32.850 --> 00:18:37.310
OK so we are back on the future
of the circular collider.

00:18:37.310 --> 00:18:40.340
In response to the upgrade of
the so-called European strategy

00:18:40.340 --> 00:18:42.610
for particle physics,
in 2013, they

00:18:42.610 --> 00:18:47.540
requested a study of a
post-LHC collider complex

00:18:47.540 --> 00:18:50.810
after the Large Hadron
Collider, based at CERN.

00:18:50.810 --> 00:18:53.420
And this would be a
larger circular ring.

00:18:53.420 --> 00:18:55.700
Here you see, the LHC
looks small, as unfiltered,

00:18:55.700 --> 00:18:57.900
but here we don't talk
about a long line.

00:18:57.900 --> 00:18:59.520
But we have another
circle, which

00:18:59.520 --> 00:19:01.440
is now 100 kilometers
in circumference, which

00:19:01.440 --> 00:19:03.520
would go around
the city of Geneva

00:19:03.520 --> 00:19:05.980
and the nearby mountain,
which is called the Saleve.

00:19:05.980 --> 00:19:08.912
And it would pass under
the lake of Geneva.

00:19:08.912 --> 00:19:09.870
We are quite fortunate.

00:19:09.870 --> 00:19:11.930
On this side-- on
the Geneva side,

00:19:11.930 --> 00:19:14.650
the lake is rather shallow,
only 15 meters deep.

00:19:14.650 --> 00:19:17.020
But on the other side, it
becomes very, very deep

00:19:17.020 --> 00:19:19.990
on the opposite side
at [? Montre ?].

00:19:19.990 --> 00:19:21.310
So there's no problem.

00:19:21.310 --> 00:19:23.660
The LHC is 100 meters
under the surface

00:19:23.660 --> 00:19:26.730
and this FCC will be 200
meters under the surface.

00:19:26.730 --> 00:19:29.230
So there's no issue
going under the lake.

00:19:29.230 --> 00:19:30.210
But we are limited.

00:19:30.210 --> 00:19:32.190
We cannot build something much
bigger than 100 kilometers

00:19:32.190 --> 00:19:34.250
because on the one side,
there are the Arabs here

00:19:34.250 --> 00:19:36.030
and on the other,
the Jura Mountain.

00:19:36.030 --> 00:19:39.780
And we don't 1000-meter-deep
access shafts.

00:19:39.780 --> 00:19:42.891
So we are somewhat limited
to this 100 kilometers.

00:19:42.891 --> 00:19:45.390
Now we would like to go up, in
energy, an order of magnitude

00:19:45.390 --> 00:19:46.500
beyond the LHC.

00:19:46.500 --> 00:19:49.490
There are reasons to believe
that going up in a factor

00:19:49.490 --> 00:19:55.250
10 or so in energy will
help us understand the Higgs

00:19:55.250 --> 00:19:56.960
mechanism-- more
properties of the Higgs

00:19:56.960 --> 00:19:58.860
particle, the
potential of the Higgs,

00:19:58.860 --> 00:20:02.250
and also perhaps help us
understand dark matter,

00:20:02.250 --> 00:20:03.810
and with luck dark energy.

00:20:03.810 --> 00:20:06.490
So to go to 100 TeV
in this larger ring,

00:20:06.490 --> 00:20:09.760
we need 16 Tesla
magnets-- dipole magnets.

00:20:09.760 --> 00:20:12.230
And the LHC has eight
tesla and that was already

00:20:12.230 --> 00:20:14.730
extremely difficult. And if
you want to go from eight tesla

00:20:14.730 --> 00:20:16.810
to 16 tesla, you need
a new technology.

00:20:16.810 --> 00:20:19.070
So we need a new type
of superconductor

00:20:19.070 --> 00:20:20.770
to make these magnets.

00:20:20.770 --> 00:20:23.350
Those are simple equations.

00:20:23.350 --> 00:20:25.490
Actually, energy of a Hadron
Collider is very easy.

00:20:25.490 --> 00:20:27.240
It's just proportional
to the magnetic field

00:20:27.240 --> 00:20:28.170
and the circumference.

00:20:28.170 --> 00:20:29.436
So we are increasing both.

00:20:29.436 --> 00:20:30.810
So we're increasing
circumference

00:20:30.810 --> 00:20:33.650
by a factor 4 almost, and we're
increasing the magnetic field

00:20:33.650 --> 00:20:36.230
by factor 2, which is
already quite challenging.

00:20:36.230 --> 00:20:40.380
And together, we get almost
a factor 8 in energy.

00:20:40.380 --> 00:20:42.110
If we builds this new
tunnel, we can also

00:20:42.110 --> 00:20:44.310
think about putting other
colliders in the standard.

00:20:44.310 --> 00:20:47.660
For example, we can put a
compositron circular collider.

00:20:47.660 --> 00:20:50.637
And that would have a
very excellent performance

00:20:50.637 --> 00:20:52.720
at energies where we can
produce a Higgs particle.

00:20:52.720 --> 00:20:54.680
So this would also be
a very beautiful Higgs

00:20:54.680 --> 00:20:57.450
factory and also a nice
factory of top quark.

00:20:57.450 --> 00:21:00.590
So we can actually produce
all the known particles,

00:21:00.590 --> 00:21:03.450
and in very large
quantities, and measure

00:21:03.450 --> 00:21:05.937
with extreme precision
to see any deviation

00:21:05.937 --> 00:21:07.770
from the standard model,
which would give us

00:21:07.770 --> 00:21:10.626
a hint at which the next energy
scale in [? new ?] physics

00:21:10.626 --> 00:21:11.780
should appear.

00:21:11.780 --> 00:21:14.510
Of course, we can also collide
electrons with protons,

00:21:14.510 --> 00:21:17.230
as we did at HERA in
Hamburg, where I started.

00:21:17.230 --> 00:21:19.470
So people who want to make
a super-HERA with it's

00:21:19.470 --> 00:21:22.650
10-times higher energy and 10
to 100-times the luminosity.

00:21:22.650 --> 00:21:24.680
So this could also be possible.

00:21:24.680 --> 00:21:27.100
And in addition, we have
a less ambitious study.

00:21:27.100 --> 00:21:28.670
We developed the
16 tesla magnets,

00:21:28.670 --> 00:21:30.240
we could install
these magnets also

00:21:30.240 --> 00:21:32.670
in the existing LHC tunnel.

00:21:32.670 --> 00:21:34.510
And that would allow
us to double the energy

00:21:34.510 --> 00:21:36.850
of the Large Hadron Collder.

00:21:36.850 --> 00:21:39.330
This is a time scale of the
large circular colliders

00:21:39.330 --> 00:21:39.831
at CERN.

00:21:39.831 --> 00:21:42.080
There was LEP that was an
electron positron collider--

00:21:42.080 --> 00:21:46.040
study's design started
in the mid-1970s.

00:21:46.040 --> 00:21:50.340
And you see, it took
more than 10 years

00:21:50.340 --> 00:21:52.030
to design and
construct it and then

00:21:52.030 --> 00:21:53.930
it operated twelve
years for physics.

00:21:53.930 --> 00:21:55.440
And there's the LHC.

00:21:55.440 --> 00:21:58.130
And this will be followed by a
high-luminosity upgrades, which

00:21:58.130 --> 00:22:02.180
is an extension of the
LHC to give 10-times

00:22:02.180 --> 00:22:04.670
the performance, which is
called the high-luminosity LHC.

00:22:04.670 --> 00:22:07.130
And so the LHC and
[INAUDIBLE] together

00:22:07.130 --> 00:22:14.070
will run for about 25, 27
years, from 2010 to about 2037.

00:22:14.070 --> 00:22:15.870
So we have about
20 years time now

00:22:15.870 --> 00:22:19.560
to develop a concept
for a future colliders.

00:22:19.560 --> 00:22:23.670
So we have started this
future circular collider

00:22:23.670 --> 00:22:27.000
design, which is four different
colliders in one study.

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:29.770
And we aim prototyping phase.

00:22:29.770 --> 00:22:32.440
If it is supported by the next
update of the [INAUDIBLE] study

00:22:32.440 --> 00:22:35.150
in 2019, we could go
into a prototyping

00:22:35.150 --> 00:22:36.190
phase at construction.

00:22:36.190 --> 00:22:38.660
And ideally, we would
like to start the physics

00:22:38.660 --> 00:22:42.630
at this new machine when the
LHC physics terminates, so

00:22:42.630 --> 00:22:45.530
in the second half of the 2030s.

00:22:45.530 --> 00:22:47.179
So we must advance
fast now because we

00:22:47.179 --> 00:22:49.720
have less time available than
had been available for the LHC.

00:22:49.720 --> 00:22:51.630
And this machine is
much bigger and it's

00:22:51.630 --> 00:22:53.810
even more advanced technology.

00:22:53.810 --> 00:22:55.380
So we don't have so much time.

00:22:55.380 --> 00:22:58.980
And our intermediate goal is to
have a solid conceptual design

00:22:58.980 --> 00:23:00.890
by the end of 2018.

00:23:00.890 --> 00:23:03.230
So we are about halfway
in this process.

00:23:03.230 --> 00:23:08.450
And we are looking at
all the items, including

00:23:08.450 --> 00:23:13.960
the construction schedule, the
cost, the key technologies,

00:23:13.960 --> 00:23:18.010
and parameter space
for operation.

00:23:18.010 --> 00:23:20.380
