accelerators that can do

00:34:08.850 --> 00:34:11.230
what I just tried to explain.

00:34:11.230 --> 00:34:14.960
And to finish on the size of
this thing-- on the left hand

00:34:14.960 --> 00:34:16.679
side, with the red
squiggle, you can

00:34:16.679 --> 00:34:20.730
see the border of the Fermi
National Accelerator Laboratory

00:34:20.730 --> 00:34:22.280
in the US.

00:34:22.280 --> 00:34:25.170
And you can see the muon
collider fitting on that site.

00:34:25.170 --> 00:34:28.179
For comparison, you
can see the LHC, that's

00:34:28.179 --> 00:34:31.949
the blue circle, the ILC, which
is the green line, or CLIC,

00:34:31.949 --> 00:34:34.760
and on the right hand side is
what used be called the VLHC.

00:34:34.760 --> 00:34:37.120
So it's, roughly
speaking, the FCC

00:34:37.120 --> 00:34:38.810
that Frank was just describing.

00:34:38.810 --> 00:34:42.030
So it's not that-- so these
are different techniques,

00:34:42.030 --> 00:34:43.940
they do slightly
different science,

00:34:43.940 --> 00:34:46.197
and I think there's
a great strength

00:34:46.197 --> 00:34:47.780
in the breadth of
science that you can

00:34:47.780 --> 00:34:49.370
do with these different things.

00:34:49.370 --> 00:34:49.850
Thank you very much.

